text: Pluméliau-Bieuzy () is a commune in the Morbihan department in Brittany, north-western France. It was established on 1 January 2019 by merger of the former communes of Pluméliau (the seat) and Bieuzy.Arrêté préfectoral 28 November 2018 ==See also== *Communes of the Morbihan department ==References== Category:Communes of Morbihan Category:States and territories established in 2019
title: Pluméliau-Bieuzy
